  <a href="#1" id="1">
   THE STORY OF SHLAUDEMAN
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Shlaudeman, who will turn 64 the week of May 17, 1990, was approached by a senior State Department official weeks ago about going to Managua but said he was not interested.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   In addition to his ambassadorial posts, Shlaudeman was the top Latin America aide to President Ford in the mid-1970s and a diplomatic trouble-shooter in Central America under President Reagan.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   When Bush telephoned him earlier the week of May 10, 1990, Shlaudeman agreed to the appointment, the U.S. official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said on May 8, 1990.
  </a>
